task.summary: basic structure graphics : Window, ViewPort, renderables (Circle, Rectangle, Sprite), Renderable System physics: MovementSystem
textures creation changed - created dummy with default constructor, then bind and set added emscripten build

emscripten build script for linux changes for updated templated SysEnt, now two system managers (1 for update, 1 for render) text rendering entity composed from bases (instead of components) - ENonMovable, EMovable, ERenderables

collision system - WIP templating simplified, added flags to GengEntity, which is virtually derived for each Exxx entity block, flags used for checking if entity was moved/rotated in order to update bound, StartTickSystem clears flags, renderables now have ref for Geom, in order to remove it when they are destroyed, transform for renderables is used in some places instead of directly changing geom's data
removed old files dirs refactored added PgonRenderable & PgonTexturedRenderable
conditional defines for disabling geng modules

Added components&systems for transformation hierarchy between entities (will be probably needed for gui) Modified systems pipeline for new flagged systems Total Renderer/Renderables overwrite: vertices not indexed anymore multiple vertex buffers for each vertex data type, also can buffers handle fragmentation (when holes size get too large they compress themselves) adding new vertices to geoms - when there free space next to it it is added inplace otherwise geometry is moved to the back and hole is created renderables are just light wrapper with reference to render task render tasks hold all relevant information for rendering (geom, uniforms ...) and are directly managed by renderer geoms have GeomState (Animation, Text, ParticleBatch), can be shared between geoms geoms can specify usage (static, dynamic, stream) which controls in which buffers they are placed vertex attribs are directly mapped to binding points via their name across shaders
Added particles Made header only lib
